<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="276" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1623,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1623,1650]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Crown (
<figureCitation box="[375,457,1624,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) pale yellow with a narrow dark macula near anterior margin. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1299,1428,1624,1650]" captionStart="FIGURES 23−32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[201,1384,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1391,166,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23−32. Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 23, head, ventral view. 24, forewing. 25, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 26, subgenital plate, ventral view. 27, connective and styles, dorsal view. 28, style, lateral view. 29−32, aedeagus. 29, lateral view. 30, caudal view. 31, ventral view. 32, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516190/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Figs 29–32</figureCitation>
) with pair of long and slender dorsally curved atrial processes, subequal in length to shaft; shaft approximately tubular and dorsally curved.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1623,2011]" box="[199,1301,1731,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,1731,1758]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Description.</emphasis>
Measurements (mm). Total length of 
<typeStatus box="[769,867,1732,1758]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">holotype</typeStatus>
7.7. Total length of 
<typeStatus box="[1094,1201,1733,1759]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">paratypes</typeStatus>
8.1−8.3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1623,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,335,1767,1794]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Coloration.</emphasis>
Pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[493,623,1768,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Fig. 41, 42</figureCitation>
). Crown (
<figureCitation box="[736,866,1768,1794]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Figs 43, 44</figureCitation>
) with a narrow dark macula near anterior margin; crown and frons with irregular orangish-yellow areas. Forewing hyaline white (
<figureCitation box="[1046,1128,1804,1830]" captionStart="FIGURES 15−22" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1932,1957]" captionTargetBox="[200,1377,184,1901]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1387,166,1912]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 15−22. Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 15, head, ventral view. 16, forewing. 17, pygofer, valve, and subgenital plate, lateral view. 18, subgenital plate, ventral view. 19, connective and styles, dorsal view. 20, style, lateral view. 21, aedeagus, lateral view. 22, aedeagus, caudal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516186" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516186/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
) with smoky marginal area at apex. Legs (
<figureCitation box="[315,442,1840,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 33−44" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1907,1932]" captionTargetBox="[225,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[209,1379,166,1887]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 33−44. 33−36, Evanirvana aurea Hill, 1973, male. 33, dorsal habitus. 34, lateral habitus. 35, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 36, head and prothorax, lateral view. 37−40, Evanirvana tambopata sp. nov., male holotype. 37, dorsal habitus. 38, lateral habitus. 39, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 40, head and prothorax, lateral view. 41−44, Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 41, dorsal habitus. 42, lateral habitus. 43, head and prothorax, dorsal view. 44, head and prothorax, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516192" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516192/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Figs 41, 42</figureCitation>
) pale yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1623,2011]" box="[199,1009,1876,1903]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,461,1876,1902]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">External morphology.</emphasis>
Same as described for genus by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dietrich, C. H." box="[828,1005,1876,1902]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276" pagination="455 - 487" refId="ref5482" refString="Dietrich, C. H. (2004) Phylogeny of the leafhopper subfamily Evacanthinae with a review of Neotropical species and notes on related groups (Hemiptera: Membracoidea: Cicadellidae). Systematic Entomology, 29, 455 - 487, https: // doi. prg / 10.1111 / j. 0307 - 6970.2004.00250. x" type="journal article" year="2004">Dietrich (2004)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1623,2011]" lastBlockId="9.[151,1437,153,647]" lastPageId="9" lastPageNumber="280" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,402,1911,1938]" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[521,606,1911,1938]" captionStart="FIGURES 23−32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[201,1384,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1391,166,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23−32. Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 23, head, ventral view. 24, forewing. 25, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 26, subgenital plate, ventral view. 27, connective and styles, dorsal view. 28, style, lateral view. 29−32, aedeagus. 29, lateral view. 30, caudal view. 31, ventral view. 32, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516190/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) longer than high; macrosetae distributed only on posterior third; apex concave. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[453,534,1947,1974]" captionStart="FIGURES 23−32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[201,1384,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1391,166,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23−32. Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 23, head, ventral view. 24, forewing. 25, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 26, subgenital plate, ventral view. 27, connective and styles, dorsal view. 28, style, lateral view. 29−32, aedeagus. 29, lateral view. 30, caudal view. 31, ventral view. 32, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516190/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
) almost extending to pygofer apex; in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1120,1203,1948,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 23−32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[201,1384,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1391,166,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23−32. Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 23, head, ventral view. 24, forewing. 25, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 26, subgenital plate, ventral view. 27, connective and styles, dorsal view. 28, style, lateral view. 29−32, aedeagus. 29, lateral view. 30, caudal view. 31, ventral view. 32, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516190/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Fig. 26</figureCitation>
), subtriangular, apex rounded. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[403,487,1984,2010]" captionStart="FIGURES 23−32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[201,1384,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1391,166,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23−32. Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 23, head, ventral view. 24, forewing. 25, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 26, subgenital plate, ventral view. 27, connective and styles, dorsal view. 28, style, lateral view. 29−32, aedeagus. 29, lateral view. 30, caudal view. 31, ventral view. 32, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516190/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Fig. 27</figureCitation>
) with short arms, stem expanded apically. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1052,1184,1984,2010]" captionStart="FIGURES 23−32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[201,1384,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1391,166,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23−32. Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 23, head, ventral view. 24, forewing. 25, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 26, subgenital plate, ventral view. 27, connective and styles, dorsal view. 28, style, lateral view. 29−32, aedeagus. 29, lateral view. 30, caudal view. 31, ventral view. 32, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516190/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="276">Figs 27, 28</figureCitation>
) with apophysis short and stout; apex hooked on inner side and with distinct short spine on outer side. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1165,1292,153,179]" captionStart="FIGURES 23−32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[201,1384,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1391,166,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23−32. Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 23, head, ventral view. 24, forewing. 25, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 26, subgenital plate, ventral view. 27, connective and styles, dorsal view. 28, style, lateral view. 29−32, aedeagus. 29, lateral view. 30, caudal view. 31, ventral view. 32, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516190/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Figs 29–32</figureCitation>
) with pair of long and slender atrial processes, strongly curved dorsally, subequal in length to shaft; shaft approximately tubular, in caudal view expanded laterally at midlength, in lateral view curved dorsally, apical third slightly expanded ventrally forming pair of small rugose flaps; apex, in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[855,938,261,287]" captionStart="FIGURES 23−32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1942,1967]" captionTargetBox="[201,1384,172,1903]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[197,1391,166,1922]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 23−32. Pentoffia santosi sp. nov., male holotype. 23, head, ventral view. 24, forewing. 25, pygofer, valve, subgenital plate, and anal tube, lateral view. 26, subgenital plate, ventral view. 27, connective and styles, dorsal view. 28, style, lateral view. 29−32, aedeagus. 29, lateral view. 30, caudal view. 31, ventral view. 32, dorsal view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3516190" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3516190/files/figure.png" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Fig. 32</figureCitation>
), rounded.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
